
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 I. Directory structure
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

llvm
     LLVM source code
build
     LLVM build directory.
     Not tracked by git.
private
     Your private directory.
     Not tracked by git.
gitsetup
     Git setup instructions and script.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 II. Building the LLVM compiler
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Execute the script config-llvm.sh in the project's root directory.

   *** You only need to do this step the first time you build the compiler.

2. Go to the build directory.

   cd build

3. Type "make" to start compilation.

   You may use multiple threads to speedup the compilation process, by
   appending the -j option.  For instance, "make -j4" launches 4 threads.

